cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SD 

This paper deals with Natural Language Understanding and proposes various models to identify if a desire expressed in a given text was fulfilled. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques and structured models, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning) likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with understanding narrative and discourse structure, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SD (Sound) possible sub-categories.
